    <summary>
      <para>
        Explains the visual appearance, usage, context menus and properties of the transition segment shape.
      </para>
    </summary>
    <introduction>
      <para>
        The transition segment shape is used to define the target states for a transition, the source states for a join transition and the initial state of a region.
        It connects to a <link xlink:href="31807e1f-17b3-484d-b250-1cc6eb0e85bf">state shape</link> to define the referenced state and to a <link xlink:href="9611a508-1db1-452a-8d6e-3ae59b29b5e1">transition knot shape</link> to define the transition.
      </para>
      <mediaLink>
        <caption placement="after" lead="Figure 1">Usage of the transition segment shape in a simple two ended transition, in a fork transition, in a join transition and attached to a state for defining the initial state</caption>
        <image placement="center" xlink:href="TransitionSegmentShapeSimpleAndForkAndJoinAndInitial"/>
      </mediaLink>
    </introduction>

