    <section address="TransitionSegmentShapeProperties">
      <title>Transition Segment Shape Properties</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          The properties dialog of the the transition segment shape can be opened either by double clicking the connector line or by opening the context menu of the connector line and executing the menu item <ui>Properties...</ui>.
        </para>
        <mediaLink>
          <caption placement="after" lead="Figure 2">Transition segment shape properties</caption>
          <image placement="center" xlink:href="TransitionSegmentShapeProperties"/>
        </mediaLink>
        <para>
          The properties are as follows:
        </para>
        <table>
          <tableHeader>
            <row>
              <entry>
                <para>Property</para>
              </entry>
              <entry>
                <para>Purpose</para>
              </entry>
            </row>
          </tableHeader>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <para>
                <ui>Segment&#160;Type</ui>
              </para>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <para>
                Switches the intention of the segment.
                Choose between <ui>From&#160;state</ui>, <ui>To&#160;state</ui> and <ui>Initial&#160;state</ui>.
                <ui>From&#160;state</ui> is used to define source states of a join transition.
                <ui>To&#160;state</ui> is used to define target states of a fork transition.
                <ui>Initial&#160;state</ui> is used to define the initial state of a region, see also <link xlink:href="29cbc4cc-2c35-40ca-b3eb-cc08ff2cd7e1">region shape</link>.
              </para>
            </entry>
          </row>
        </table>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section address="TransitionSegmentShapeContextMenu">
      <title>Transition Segment Shape Context Menu</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          The transition segment shape has the following additional context menu items:
        </para>
        <table>
          <tableHeader>
